{
  "buggy_files": ["drivers/platform/x86/acer-wmi.c"],
  "buggy_functions": ["video_vendor_dmi_table"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Acer TravelMate 5735Z is missing from the video_vendor_dmi_table in acer-wmi.c. This DMI table contains entries for Acer machines that should use the native/ACPI video backlight driver instead of acer-wmi's brightness interface. When a device is not in this table but has an entry in acer_quirks (or falls back to quirk_unknown), the acer-wmi driver enables ACER_CAP_BRIGHTNESS capability and registers a brightness backlight device. This interferes with the native backlight (intel_backlight) from working properly. Other similar Acer TravelMate models like 4750 and 5760 are already in this table. The bug report confirms the hardware supports native backlight since acpi_backlight=native parameter makes it work correctly. The fix is to add an entry for TravelMate 5735Z to video_vendor_dmi_table with callback video_set_backlight_video_vendor to disable brightness capability and allow native backlight to function."
}

